12/06/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- EU Enlargement Commissioner Guenter Verheugen is optimistic about Romania's prospects for completing pre-accession talks with the Union in 2004.
During a recent meeting of the EU-Romania joint parliamentary committee in Brussels, he reportedly gave a positive assessment of results achieved so far, suggesting that if the current pace is maintained, the goal of EU membership in 2007 could be met.
In other news, during an official visit Wednesday to Bucharest, Spain's King Juan Carlos I expressed strong support for Romania's EU and NATO aspirations.
He and his wife, Queen Sofia, attended an official dinner given by President Ion Iliescu.
(Nine o'Clock - 12/06/03)
